      "title": "Friendly consonants",
      "subtitle": "aasaan vyanjan",
      "goal": "Build confidence with the consonants that sound almost exactly like English.",
      "intro": "Good news, many Hindi consonants are basically English. Each letter carries a built-in 'a', so 'k' is said 'ka'. Tap to hear the sound, then the word.",
