    {
      "id": "special-sounds",
      "order": 4,
      "title": "Special sounds (ṛ, sh, nasal)",
      "subtitle": "vishesh dhwani",
      "goal": "Pick up the flap ṛ, the 'sh' sounds, and Hindi's nasal hum.",
      "intro": "A few last sounds with no clean English match. The flap 'ṛ' is a quick flick of the tongue. The nasal hum 'ñ' (written ं or ँ) sends the sound through your nose. Listen and feel where each one buzzes.",
